Neighbor Cell RCA Analysis Algorithm
Objective
To determine whether an anomalous cell issue is:
Cell-level
Site-level / Infrastructure-related
Traffic congestion-related
Low-confidence due to missing data
by analyzing spatial neighbors within a temporal observation window.

Inputs
1.Dataset 
dataset containing records with fields:

Field	          Description	               Used in Algorithm

timestamp	      Measurement time	           Window filtering
record_id	      Unique record identifier	   Reference only
cell_id	          Cell identifier	           Primary key
site_id	          Physical site ID	           Contextual RCA
technology	      LTE / NR / etc	           Optional filtering
vendor	          Equipment vendor	           Optional analysis
bandwidth	      Channel bandwidth	           Context only
capacity	      Maximum capacity	           Context only
neighbors	      Neighbor cell list	       Alternative neighbor source
active_users	  Connected users	           Congestion context
prb_dl	          Downlink PRB utilization (%) Load metric
prb_ul	          Uplink PRB utilization (%)   Optional
sinr	          Signal quality	           Optional RCA extension
rsrp	          Signal strength	           Optional RCA extension
throughput_dl	  Downlink throughput	       Optional
throughput_ul	  Uplink throughput	           Optional
call_attempts	  Total call attempts	       Optional KPI
call_success	  Successful calls	           Optional KPI
ran_dcr	Drop      call rate	                   Optional degradation KPI
ran_afr	Access    failure rate	               Optional degradation KPI
availability	  Cell availability (%)	       Health metric
is_anomaly	      Anomaly flag	               RCA trigger

2 Anomalous Record A
Single record identified as anomalous:
A = (cell_id, timestamp)

3 Neighbor Map N
Mapping of serving cell → neighboring cells.
Example:
CELL-027 → [CELL-026, CELL-028, CELL-029]

4 Parameters
Parameter	    Value	Description
window_minutes	10	    Temporal analysis window
records_limit	10	    Maximum records per neighbor

Algorithm
Step 1 — Dataset Preparation
Load dataset.
Convert timestamps into datetime format.
Validate required columns:
[cell_id, timestamp, prb_dl, availability, is_anomaly]

Step 2 — Neighbor Identification
Given anomalous cell:
C_anomaly = A.cell_id
T_anomaly = A.timestamp
Retrieve neighbors:
Neighbors = N[C_anomaly]
If no neighbors exist:
Neighbor Status = Unknown
Terminate analysis

Step 3 — Temporal Neighbor Data Extraction
Define analysis window:
T_start = T_anomaly − window_minutes
For each neighbor cell Ci:
Filter dataset:
Ci records where:
    cell_id == Ci
    AND T_start ≤ timestamp ≤ T_anomaly
Sort by newest timestamp.
Select last records_limit entries.
Classification:
If records exist → valid neighbor dataset
If empty → mark as missing neighbor

Step 4 — Combine Neighbor Records
Merge all valid neighbor datasets:
Neighbor Dataset = UNION(all neighbor records)
If combined dataset is empty:
Neighbor Status = Unknown
Terminate analysis

Step 5 — Compute Key Metrics
Metric 1 — Average Neighbor PRB (DL)
Measures surrounding traffic load.
Avg_PRB =
    mean(prb_dl)
Metric 2 — Average Neighbor Availability
Measures service health around anomaly.
Avg_Availability =
    mean(availability)
Metric 3 — Neighbor Anomaly Count
Indicates anomaly propagation.
Neighbor_Anomaly_Count =
    count(is_anomaly == True)
Metric 4 — Data Completeness
Missing_Neighbors =
    neighbors without records   

Step 6 — Neighbor Status Classification
Decision rules:
1. Unknown
IF no neighbor data available
2. Partial Data
IF some neighbors missing
3. Congested
IF Avg_PRB ≥ 80%
Interpretation: high traffic load.   
4. Degraded
IF Avg_Availability < 95%
Interpretation: service degradation.
5. Normal
IF Availability ≥ 95%
AND PRB < 80%
Interpretation: neighbors healthy. 

Step 7 — RCA Interpretation Logic

Neighbor Status	     Root Cause Interpretation

Normal	             Issue isolated to anomalous cell
Degraded	         Possible site-level or infrastructure failure
Congested	         Traffic overload or traffic shift
Partial Data	     Reduced RCA confidence
Unknown	             Insufficient information

Step 8 — Output Generation

The algorithm returns structured RCA output:

{
  anomaly_cell,
  analysis_time,
  neighbors_checked,
  missing_neighbors,
  avg_neighbor_prb_dl,
  avg_neighbor_availability,
  neighbor_anomaly_count,
  neighbor_status,
  rca_interpretation
}

High-Level Algorithm Flow:-----

Detect Anomaly
        ↓
Find Neighbor Cells
        ↓
Collect Neighbor Time Window Data
        ↓
Merge Neighbor Records
        ↓
Compute Metrics
        ↓
Classify Neighbor Health
        ↓
Generate RCA Interpretation